<h3 id="side-by-side-comparison">Side-by-Side Comparison</h3>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>SGCraft</th>
      <th>AUNIS</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Has a Pegasus portal</td>
      <td>Has a Universe portal</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Portal is easier to build (square, no directionality)</td>
      <td>Portal is bigger</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Less JEI clutter, fewer pointless upgrades</td>
      <td>More fluid crafting, microcrafting</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>UI is easier to access and interact with</td>
      <td>UI is more immersive</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>You can camouflage the portalâ€™s base</td>
      <td>You can camouflage most of the portalâ€™s base</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>ComputerCraft integration</td>
      <td>Built-in exploration mechanic (Mysterious Pages)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Photorealistic textures</td>
      <td>Cleaner textures</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>SGCraft Pros:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Can type dialing sequence on keyboard</li>
  <li>Both UIs are accessible from any side</li>
  <li>You can reskin portals with an upgrade, no need to rebuild</li>
</ul>

